> On Fri, May 2, 2008 at 11:00 AM, John A. Kunze <jak@ucop.edu> wrote:
> 
> > --- On Fri, 25 Apr 2008, Hayward Lam wrote:
> > > Library and Archives Canada is looking into using Ark for digital
> > > repository. I have read your paper and IETF draft spec. I have a few
> > > questions I hope you know the answers:
> >
> > Dear Hayward,
> >
> > Apologies for my delayed response -- busy travel schedule lately and
> > preparing for a persistent identifier and resolver workshop in two
> > weeks at the National Library of Sweden.
> >
> > > 1) Is there a Ark community forum/mailing list to bounce idea?
> >
> > Not yet.  We've never done any marketing, but ARK usage is up and
> > people have been asking for a mailing list.  It's pretty clear
> > that this has to be set up.
> >
> > > 2) Is there a recommendation/experience on how to organize collections
> > and
> > > Ark ids?
> >
> > There's plenty of prior art that meets various local objectives, but
> > little experience has been shared.  It's been a feature all along that
> > ARKs let you do what you want, but that much blank canvas can be scary
> > without a few usage scenarios as concrete examples to react to.  The
> > BnF has suggested that we should develop a training module that will
> > help institutions make their decisions.  I'll be presenting something
> > at ALA in June that starts to sketch this area out.
> >
> > > 3) In the ARK spec:
> > >
> > > If the ARK contains an internal slash after the NAAN, the piece to its
> > left
> > > indicates a
> > > containing object. For example, publishing an ARK of the form,
> > >
> > > ark:/12025/654/xz/321
> > >
> > > is equivalent to publishing three ARKs,
> > >
> > > ark:/12025/654/xz/321
> > > ark:/12025/654/xz
> > > ark:/12025/654
> > >
> > > Does it mean the followings should all return corresponding metadata
> > > records?
> > >
> > > ark:/12025/654/xz/321?
> > > ark:/12025/654/xz?
> > > ark:/12025/654?
> >
> > Yes.  While it's important that the root ARK (654) respond to '?',
> > the burden of responding similarly to all the extended ARKs (eg, 654/xz)
> > can be made more bearable in a number of ways.  The simplest temporary
> > (or permanent) solution is probably to respond as if '654/xz?' was really
> > '654?', under the belief that returning something (the parent record) is
> > better than nothing.
> >
> > Short of detailed information about each component, it should also be
> > possible to insert a generic qualifier (eg, "part of") in front of the
> > parent record.  We're not certain what that should look like, but would
> > be quite interested in discussing it with you.
> >
> > Thanks very much for writing.  Let me know if you'd like a NAAN to
> > use as look into this further.
> >
> > -John
